The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                  BRIEFS

         
	Tamluk, Feb. 26: Eight trucks loaded with iron dust were seized in Tamluk town on Monday night. 
  
	Police said the trucks were carrying the dust that arrived by train from Jharkhand for Haldia, but dumping them here because of lack of space in the port town. Residents had been complaining for over a year against the practice that leads to severe air pollution.
    
	Howrah: A fire broke out at a vegetable oil factory in an industry hub in Sankrail, 30km from Calcutta, on Tuesday evening. Eight fire engines with 100 firefighters put out the blaze in the complex with around 150 oil-making units.
    
	Santiniketan: Scholar, poet and former chief of Rabindra Bhavan museum Shibnarayan Roy died this morning after a heart attack. He was 87. Roy is survived by wife Gita, son, daughter and daughter-in-law. He had started preparing the catalogue of items on display at the museum, said a Visva-Bharati spokesperson.
    
	Durgapur: Two more persons have been arrested in connection with last Wednesdays incident in which truck driver Abodh Kishore Singh was burnt alive by a mob at Burnpur near Asansol. His vehicle had run over a schoolboy.
                                                                               
